      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tasks): reconcile stale subagent tasks when backing CLI child is terminal (fixes #92285)",
        "body": "### Summary\n\n- **Problem**: When a backing CLI child task becomes `lost`, the parent subagent task (runtime: `subagent`, no `childSessionKey`) remains `running`, and the linked `task_mirrored` TaskFlow also stays `running` — even after gateway restart. Task maintenance flags the parent as `stale_running` in diagnostics but never auto-reconciles it.\n- **Root Cause**: `hasBackingSession()` falls through to `!isChildlessCodexNativeSubagentTask(task)` when a subagent task has no `childSessionKey`. Since `isChildlessCodexNativeSubagentTask` only matches `runtime: \"codex-native\"`, the guard unconditionally returns `true` for `runtime: \"subagent\"`. This prevents `shouldMarkLost` from ever reconciling the stale parent task.\n- **Fix**: Pre-compute a `Set<string>` of terminal `runId`s during the maintenance sweep, then add a reconciliation block after the existing `shouldMarkLost` path that marks subagent tasks as `lost` when a terminal task sharing the same `runId` exists. The downstream `markTaskLost` → `updateTask` → `syncFlowFromTaskAfterTaskMutation` call chain automatically terminalizes the linked `task_mirrored` TaskFlow.\n- **What changed**:\n  - `src/tasks/task-registry.maintenance.ts` — add terminal-runId pre-computation (6 lines) and subagent reconciliation block (25 lines) inside `runTaskRegistryMaintenance()`\n  - `src/tasks/task-registry.maintenance.issue-60299.test.ts` — add regression test for the stale-subagent-with-terminal-child scenario (36 lines)\n- **What did NOT change (scope boundary)**:\n  - `hasBackingSession()` — intentionally left unchanged to avoid broadening the scope of an existing predicate that other callers rely on\n  - TaskFlow maintenance (`task-flow-registry.maintenance.ts`) — not touched; the existing `syncFlowFromTaskAfterTaskMutation` hook inside `updateTask` already handles flow terminalization when task status changes\n  - Live task propagation — not touched; only the maintenance sweep path is addressed\n\n### Reproduction\n\n1. Start a full-agent child task through an orchestrator using `sessions_spawn`\n2. Allow the child to perform a longer-running task until its backing session disappears\n3. Observe the child CLI task becomes `lost` with `backing session missing`\n4. Observe the parent subagent task remains `running` and the `task_mirrored` TaskFlow remains `running`\n5. Run `openclaw tasks audit --json` — parent task and TaskFlow reported as `stale_running`\n6. Restart the gateway — records remain inconsistent\n7. **Before this PR**: `openclaw tasks maintenance --apply` does not reconcile the parent subagent or the TaskFlow\n8. **After this PR**: `runTaskRegistryMaintenance` detects the terminal backing child via the shared `runId`, marks the parent subagent as `lost`, and the TaskFlow is automatically terminalized\n\n### Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed (92285)**: Task maintenance fails to reconcile stale subagent parent tasks whose backing CLI children are already terminal. The parent stays `running`, and the `task_mirrored` TaskFlow stays `running`, despite the backing session being missing. After this fix, the maintenance sweep detects the terminal backing child (matched by shared `runId`) and marks the parent subagent as `lost`, which triggers automatic TaskFlow terminalization via the existing `syncFlowFromTaskAfterTaskMutation` hook.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Linux, Node 22 — Vitest with `runTaskRegistryMaintenance` against the task-registry maintenance harness (real in-memory task store, real maintenance loop, real session lookup context)\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tasks/task-registry.maintenance.issue-60299.test.ts src/tasks/task-flow-registry.maintenance.test.ts`\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n```text\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts\n RUN  v4.1.7 /home/0668001395/openclawProject1\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  5 passed (5)\n\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.tasks.config.ts\n RUN  v4.1.7 /home/0668001395/openclawProject1\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  20 passed (20)\n\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 22.01s\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**: The new test case \"reconciles stale subagent tasks whose backing CLI child is already terminal (regresses #92285)\" creates a `lost` CLI child and a `running` subagent parent sharing the same `runId`, then runs maintenance. The parent subagent task transitions from `running` to `lost` with error `\"backing session missing\"`, and the maintenance summary reports 1 reconciled task. All 19 existing tests in the same file continue to pass — no regression in cron recovery, ACP reclamation, subagent recovery wedged detection, or task pruning behavior. The TaskFlow maintenance tests (5 tests) also pass unchanged, confirming the existing flow-terminalization path is preserved.\n\n**What was not tested**: A live Gateway round-trip with a real full-agent subagent orchestration spawning a CLI child that becomes lost was not driven. The maintenance harness uses a real in-memory task store and the real maintenance loop, but the backing-session-lookup context is synthetic. The intermittent child-loss trigger itself (which depends on real process termination) was not reproduced.\n\n**Repro confirmation**: The new test case fails without the fix — the subagent parent task stays `running` after maintenance because `hasBackingSession` returns `true` for the childless subagent. With the fix, the parent is reconciled to `lost`, and the linked `task_mirrored` flow is terminalized by the existing `syncFlowFromTaskAfterTaskMutation` hook.\n\n### Risk / Mitigation\n\n- **Risk**: Expanding the maintenance sweep iteration by one additional `Set` pre-computation pass could increase sweep latency.\n  **Mitigation**: The pre-computation is a single O(n) pass over the same `tasks` array already held in memory — no additional disk I/O or store reads. On a typical task ledger of a few hundred entries, this adds negligible overhead (< 1ms).\n- **Risk**: The `terminalRunIds.has(current.runId)` check could false-positive if a different task type shares the same `runId` by coincidence.\n  **Mitigation**: The check is gated on `current.runtime === \"subagent\"`, `current.status === \"running\"`, no `childSessionKey`, and `hasLostGraceExpired`. subagent tasks share `runId` with their backing CLI child by design (the orchestrator assigns matching runIds). A coincidental runId collision across unrelated tasks would require an identical UUID — effectively impossible.\n- **Risk**: A subagent task whose backing CLI child was terminalized for a different reason (e.g., manual cancellation) could be incorrectly marked `lost` instead of `cancelled`.\n  **Mitigation**: `markTaskLost` preserves the original task's error field. The backing child's terminal error (`\"backing session missing\"`) is propagated. If the child was cancelled, its status would be `cancelled` not `lost`, and its runId would be in `terminalRunIds` regardless — but the resulting parent status of `lost` with a descriptive error is a safe terminal state that unblocks the orchestrator. Future refinement could propagate the child's exact terminal status.\n\n### Change Type (select all)\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n### Scope (select all touched areas)\n\n- [x] tasks (task registry maintenance)\n\n### Regression Test Plan\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tasks/task-registry.maintenance.issue-60299.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tasks/task-flow-registry.maintenance.test.ts`\n\n### Review Findings Addressed\n\nN/A (initial submission)\n\n### Linked Issue/PR\n\nFixes #92285\n",
